      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 1,
      "creation_date" : 1332970221,
      "post_id" : 4054277,
      "comment_id" : 12654476,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Executors will swallow thrown exceptions that you don&#39;t specifically handle in your Callable/Runnable.  If your Runnable/Callable doesn&#39;t catch and handle the exception itself and it is provided to you vs you owning it, then you need to subclass the ScheduledExecutorService and override afterExecute (make sure to call super.afterExecute()).  The second argument to afterExecute will be the throwable from the Runnable/Callable"
    } ],
