      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@thecoshman - the timer implementations do NOT interrupt the DB operation once it is in progress, nor does this.  In any case, you can only control the time that you start the DB operation.  There is a common misconception that you need a &quot;timer&quot; in order to time things, but you don&#39;t.  You need only to DO something, and by using the current time make sure you don&#39;t DO IT too long."
